OL,3,CWoman who saved boy, 15, from drowning
OL,4,Cissues water safety warning
OL,6,F"I am eternally grateful for Natalie
OL,7,Frisking her life to save him," the
OL,8,Fboy's mother told ITV Border, "the
OL,9,Fdoctors have made it clear he was
OL,10,Fextremely lucky to survive as tests
OL,11,Fshowed his brain was without oxygen
OL,12,Ffor a significant amount of time.
OL,14,F"There is no doubt that if Natalie had
OL,15,Fnot jumped in to rescue him, he would
OL,16,Fnot be here today. She is an absolute
OL,17,Fangel."
